    continue;
}

if (chan->state == BT_CONNECT) {
    if (!status)
        l2cap_start_connection(chan);
    else
        __set_chan_timer(chan, L2CAP_DISC_TIMEOUT);
}
```

These sections do not involve any direct manipulation of the control request data or its length. They handle state transitions and operations based on the current state of the channel and the security status.

### Conclusion

Based on the analysis, the provided code snippet does not contain the specific behavior of blindly using the `wLength` field from the control request without proper validation. Therefore, it does not exhibit the same vulnerability behavior as described in the vulnerability knowledge.

